&lt;h3&gt;About Ahrefs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ahrefs is a SaaS marketing platform that helps businesses become discoverable and unmissable online. We offer a suite of tools for SEO, content marketing, and website performance — backed by 15 years of web crawling data and increasingly powered by AI to deliver strategic insights at scale. We&#39;re bootstrapped, profitable, multinational, and fully remote. Our culture is fast-moving, low-ego, and built on smart decisions and ownership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll lead the marketing strategy and creative execution for Ahrefs&#39; European events program, and play a central creative role in Ahrefs Evolve — our global annual conference series. This isn&#39;t a pure logistics role: you&#39;re the person who helps shape how Ahrefs shows up at events visually and strategically, from audience campaigns to booth design to swag.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll report to the Global Head of Events (US-based) and work closely alongside our Global Partnerships &amp;amp; Revenue Manager (SG-based) on Evolve sponsorship activations and European &amp;amp; US sponsored events. For fulfillment and operational execution, you&#39;ll partner closely with our Singapore-based Event Operations Manager. You own the creative brief and speaker relationships; they own making it happen on the ground.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead event marketing strategy and execution — audience targeting, multi-channel campaigns (email, social, partnerships, content), registration drives, and post-event follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the single point of contact for Ahrefs Evolve confirmed speakers — from the moment a booking is made by the influencer team through to post-event follow-up. Speakers should never need to wonder who to contact: you own the relationship, the briefing, and the experience. You&#39;ll relay logistics requirements to the Event Operations Manager so speakers deal with one person throughout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own creative direction for Evolve, our global annual conference — including fabrication, booth design, and overall brand experience, briefing and working closely with designers across Europe and Asia.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage sponsorship booth design and creative for European field events and regional activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead swag creative direction: concept, design standards, and brand alignment — coordinating with the Event Operations Manager, who owns vendor management and fulfillment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the Global Head of Events and Global Partnerships &amp;amp; Revenue Manager on Evolve strategy and sponsorship activation planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage timelines and creative vendor relationships across multiple concurrent projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain relationships with regional communities, partners, and event venues across Europe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide cross-regional creative support for select events in Singapore and the US, ensuring consistency across all markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report on event performance — attendance, engagement, brand impact, and ROI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;You&#39;ll Thrive Here If&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve run B2B field marketing programs or event portfolios with both large-scale and grassroots activations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re a strong event marketer with solid creative instincts — you understand audience segmentation, campaign mechanics, and how to build an experience that drives registration and engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve managed fabrication, booth design, or brand experience at events — you know how to brief designers, hold vendors to a standard, and translate a brand into a physical space.&lt;/li&gt;
