&lt;h3&gt;About Ahrefs&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ahrefs is a SaaS marketing platform that helps businesses become discoverable and unmissable online. We&#39;re a proudly bootstrapped, profitable, lean, multinational startup with a global team passionate about technology and the future of online discovery. Our suite of tools covers everything from search marketing to content strategy, backed by one of the largest datasets in the industry (3 trillion external backlinks, 3 trillion HTML snapshots). As we evolve with AI and the changing landscape of online marketing, we&#39;re looking for people who share our love of technology and our drive to solve real problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Script Writer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our video team in Cambridge, MA. You&#39;ll be writing scripts and voiceovers for our YouTube channel, specifically the technical videos our current team finds hardest to crack. Think: AI tool comparisons, automation workflows, testing every image generator on the market. As we branch deeper into AI, there&#39;s more than enough work, and we need someone who can translate complex concepts into clear, engaging scripts without dumbing them down. You&#39;ll also be a self-starter who stays plugged into the market, pitches video ideas, and helps shape what we cover next.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write scripts for technical YouTube videos, AI tools, automation demos, in-depth product tests.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run your own tests and experiments when a script requires hands-on validation (e.g. &quot;I tested 12 AI writing tools — here&#39;s what actually works&quot;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and record voiceover for higher-lift technical videos that require explaining APIs, workflows, or emerging AI concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay on top of the AI and marketing tool landscape, what&#39;s launching, what&#39;s overhyped, what our audience needs to know.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pitch video ideas to the team based on market trends, audience questions, and gaps in our coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with video editors and producers to refine scripts based on visual storytelling needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI assistants and tools to speed up research, build small demos, or clarify technical details.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;You&#39;ll Thrive Here If&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can explain technical concepts (APIs, automation, AI models) clearly without being an engineer yourself.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;ve written for video before, you understand pacing, hooks, and how a script needs to serve the edit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re a self-starter who doesn&#39;t wait for assignments, you notice what&#39;s happening in the market and come to the team with ideas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re comfortable running your own tests and demos to validate what you&#39;re writing about (e.g. signing up for tools, running workflows, documenting results).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have a good working knowledge of AI tools, how to use them to build small apps, streamline research, or pull together demos.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can work autonomously and make judgment calls about tone, depth, and structure without constant check-ins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Bonus&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience writing or producing content about SEO, marketing tools or SaaS products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with scripting or light coding (even just enough to understand what an API call does or how to automate a task)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A portfolio of technical explainer videos, tutorials, or demos you&#39;ve scripted or produced&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We Offer&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work directly with a fast-moving video team on content that reaches millions of marketers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership over technical video strategy as we pu

&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First and foremost, this role is based out of our Acton, MA office. You must be able to get to Acton on a daily basis to work in-person and collaborate with the rest of the video team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Video Producer who thrives in the controlled chaos of production, someone who can lock down transport, accommodation, and kit before breakfast, then spend the afternoon shaping an edit with the team. You&#39;ll be the operational backbone of our YouTube content operation, ensuring every shoot (whether it&#39;s a multi-day location production or a nimble studio session) runs on time, on budget, and without drama.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success here means the crew never wonders where they&#39;re meant to be, the talent always has what they need, and the creative work can happen because the logistics are bulletproof. You&#39;ll work closely with the Head of Video and a small team of editors and producer/editors, juggling multiple projects while keeping your eye on the creative vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
